Mauritiusâ€™s inflation will average
5.8 percent this year, according to a central bank survey
conducted last month, up from the 5.6 percent forecast in
February.  The inflation rate will vary between 5 percent and 7
percent in December, according to 67 percent of respondents in
the survey, the Port Louis-based Bank of Mauritius said on its
website today.  Inflation accelerated to 4.8 percent in May from 4.4
percent the month before, the  Central Statistics Office  said on
